      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-06-13T18:05:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "OK, good to hear that it probably wouldn\u0027t be a bug.\n\nI\u0027m still a little nervous about converting code that would have worked for any value of numLocations into code with a fixed limit.  But if the constructor is only ever called with the default argument (as it must be if eliminating it compiles), then I guess it\u0027s only a theoretical problem.",
      "parentUuid": "8f09f4df_84018731",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 71,
        "startChar": 34,
        "endLine": 71,
